The world of Dark Pawns is a dark fantasy setting, originally conceived by Derek
L. Karnes (Serapis) and expanded over six years of continuous development.


The gods have always been, and always will be. And having free will, given to
them by Chaos, they created their own and brought forth likenesses, who strive
to become as gods, and join them in their omnipotence.

Like a great game of chess, the world has become a board filled with bishops and
kings, stately queens, white knights and dark pawns striving to rise through the
ranks into godhood.

Outside those thick walls that enable 'civilized' persons to sleep so well lies an
untamed land, some partly still ruled by the power of fangs, claws, and magic.

Twisted and warped by forgotten times into a vision that would make any sane man's
nightmare seem like a pleasant summer daydream.

Beware the unseen, adventurer. The power is there, cloaked in a forgotten tomb or
a dragon's hoard, but it is there.

  --The letter of Friar Drake to the cities of Kir Drax'in, Kir-oshi, and
    Alaozar, circa 185


The known world stretches across two continents and oceans, with the free city of
Kir Drax'in serving as a central hub for trade, training, and adventure. The
Wyldlands to the north are a magick-rich untamed wilderness where dreams become
real and the fabric of reality is thin.


Six base classes await the aspiring adventurer: Thief, Cleric, Warrior, Mage,
Ninja, and Psionic. Those who prove themselves may remort into one of six
advanced classes: Assassin, Avatar, Magus, Paladin, Ranger, or Mystic.

Seven races inhabit the world: Human, Elf, Dwarf, Kender, Minotaur, Rakshasa,
and Ssaur. Each has unique traits, languages, and homelands.

The world holds 10,057 rooms across 95 zones, guarded by 1,313 mobiles and
holding 1,661 unique objects. Explore at your own risk.
